The paper deals with graph isomorphism and its restricted version, list restricted graph isomorphism. The paper discusses combinatorial algorithms for various classes of graphs, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses group theory and its limitations in solving ListIso, which suggests that it may belong to cs.GT (Group Theory) as well. The paper also mentions bounded treewidth graphs and interval graphs, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) respectively.
